  "description": "MinimalPairs currently only trains *listening* discrimination ‚Äî users hear one of two contrasting words (e.g., light/right, base/vase) and pick which one. For Japanese learners, the *production* side of these contrasts (L/R, B/V, S/TH, etc.) is an even bigger fluency blocker. Add a new 'Speak the Pair' mode toggle on frontend/src/pages/MinimalPairs.tsx and a new component frontend/src/components/MinimalPairsSpeakMode.tsx that drills production:\n\nFlow per round (5 rounds/session, reusing pickRandomSet / startMinimalPairListening pool so no backend change is required):\n1. Show both words side by side with IPA and a üîä TTS button each (uses existing useSpeechSynthesis).\n2. The app randomly TARGETS one of the two words and asks the user to say it (e.g., 'Say: RIGHT (not light)').\n3. User taps mic ‚Üí useSpeechRecognition (lang='en-US', continuous=false, interimResults=false) captures one utterance.\n4. Score the attempt: normalize transcript to lowercase letters; if it matches the target word ‚Üí ‚úÖ 'Clear contrast!'; if it matches the *other* word in the pair ‚Üí ‚ùå 'Sounded like \"<other>\" ‚Äî try again'; otherwise ‚Üí ‚öÝÔ∏è 'Couldn't catch that, retry'. Allow up to 2 retries before auto-advance, tracking first-try success.\n5. After each round play TTS of BOTH words back-to-back at 0.85x so the user can hear the contrast they just produced.\n6. End-of-session results card: per-pair first-try accuracy, the contrast label (e.g., 'L vs R'), a 'Drill the misses' button that re-runs only failed pairs, and total stars (‚≠ê ‚â•80%, ‚≠ê‚≠ê ‚â•90%, ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê 100%).\n\nUI integration: at the top of MinimalPairs add a segmented toggle [üëÇ Listen | üé§ Speak] (default Listen, persist last choice in localStorage key 'mp_mode'). When Speak is selected, render <MinimalPairsSpeakMode contrast={contrast} pairs={rounds} onRestart={startSession} />. Reuse the existing contrast/round data (the round's word_a/word_b/ipa_a/ipa_b are sufficient ‚Äî ignore 