  "description": "Add a new Home-page tile 'Listening Warmup' that runs a hands-free 60-second passive listening session before the user dives into practice. Diversifies away from saturated Pronunciation/Conversation work and adds a fresh listening-skill entry point on Home (which is in the preferred list).\n\nBehavior:\n1. Tile shows a headphones icon, label '60s Listening Warmup', and an estimate of how many sentences will play.\n2. On click, opens a lightweight modal (or inline panel) `ListeningWarmup` component that fetches up to 6 example sentences from the user's recent vocabulary via the existing `GET /vocabulary?topic=<recent>` endpoint (or reuses `localStorage` cached words from the Vocabulary page; fall back to a small built-in fallback list of 6 sentences if no vocab is available so the feature works for new users).\n3. Each sentence is played via `speechSynthesis` at rate 0.85 first, then immediately again at rate 1.0. The current sentence text is shown large and centered; the next sentence is dimmed below it. Auto-advances when each utterance ends (via `utterance.onend`). A circular progress ring shows elapsed time / total.\n4. Buttons: Pause/Resume, Skip (next sentence), Stop (closes modal). ESC also closes.\n5. On completion, show a small summary: 'You listened to N sentences (~Xs)' and a 'Practice now' button that closes the warmup. Persist `lastWarmupAt` and `warmupStreak` (consecutive days) to `localStorage` and show a tiny streak badge on the Home tile (e.g., 'üî• 3').\n\nFiles to modify:\n- `frontend/src/components/ListeningWarmup.tsx` (new) ‚Äî the modal/panel component, ~150 lines. Uses `speechSynthesis`, refs to track current utterance for pause/cancel, accepts `sentences: string[]` prop and `onClose` callback.\n- `frontend/src/pages/Home.tsx` ‚Äî add the tile in the existing quick-action grid; manage open/close state; load sentences (try vocabulary cache, else fallback). Compute and display warmup streak from localStorage.\n- `frontend/src/__tests__/ListeningWarmup.test.tsx` (new) ‚Äî Vitest + RTL tests: (a) renders first sentence on mount, (b) clicking Skip advances to next sentence, (c) clicking Stop calls onClose, (d) shows completion summary after last sentence ends (simulate `onend`), (e) falls back gracefully to fallback sentences when prop is empty. Mock `window.speechSynthesis` and `SpeechSynthesisUtterance` like other listening tests in the repo.\n- `frontend/src/__tests__/Home.test.tsx` ‚Äî add a test that the new 'Listening Warmup' tile is rendered and clicking it opens the warmup panel.\n\nNo backend changes, no DB migration. Pure frontend. Follows existing patterns of speechSynthesis use in `VocabContextListenDrill.tsx`.",
